  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Projet d&#x2019;urgence pour faire face &#xE0; la flamb&#xE9;e de la Fi&#xE8;vre de la Vall&#xE9;e du Rift au Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide food security assistance to people affected by Rift Valley Fever (RFV) in Kirundo, Ngozi, Muyinga regions in Burundi. This FAO project reduces the spread of RVF and its negative impact on food security and livelihoods. The project provides humanitarian assistance to 78,000 people, including 30,700 women, 30,700 men, 16,600 children, and including 8,200 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
